column5: I have been fishing out of the Armstrong area for over 25 years. After getting on walleye central, I have learned that the Nakina outposts pricing is guite abit lower than out of Armstrong. The outposts seem to be fishing about the same areas. Does anyone know why the cost is lower out of Nakina?
Possibly to draw more clients to Nakina. The outpost seem to be more rustic and maybe shorter flights? Just a guess on my part. This is a good question for Mike Borger.
